<style>
	textarea {
		display: none;
		width: 100%;
		height: 10rem;
	}
	.main a.button {
		border: none;
		background: rgb(164, 237, 186);
		border-top: 3px solid transparent;
		width: auto;
		text-decoration: none;
		padding: 0.5rem;
		border-radius: 0.25rem;
	}
</style>

<div class="main">

	<h1>Share, how?</h1>

	<h2>Stable demo (preferred)</h2>
	<p>
		Fiddle with demo files from GitHub master branch and Highcharts from latest stable (code.highcharts.com).
	</p>
	<a class="button" href="https://jsfiddle.net/gh/get/library/pure/highcharts/highcharts/tree/master/samples/{{path}}/"
		target="_blank">jsFiddle</a>


	<h2>Work in progress</h2>
	<p>
		For non-techies, nice and clean preview with no code view, but contains a link to post it further to jsFiddle. Demo files and Highcharts both from latest commit (github.highcharts.com/{{latestCommit}}).
	</p>
	<a class="button" href="https://highcharts.github.io/highcharts-utils/samples/#gh/{{latestCommit}}/sample/{{path}}"
		target="_blank">highcharts.github.io</a>
	</p>

	<h2>Local work in progress</h2>
	<form method="post" action="https://jsfiddle.net/api/post/library/pure/"
			id="jsfiddle-post" target="_blank">
		<input type="hidden" name="title" value="{{title}}"/>
		<textarea name="html">{{{html}}}</textarea>
		<textarea name="js">{{{js}}}</textarea>
		<textarea name="css">{{{css}}}</textarea>
	</form>
	<p>
		Fiddle with demo files posted from your file system and Highcharts from latest commit (github.highcharts.com/{{latestCommit}}).
	</p>
	<a class="button" href="javascript:document.getElementById('jsfiddle-post').submit()">
		jsFiddle
	</a>

	<h2>Link for testing on local network</h2>
	<a class="button" href="http://{{ipAddress}}:3030/samples/view?path={{path}}">
		Right click to copy
	</a>
</div>